1
00:00:00,210 --> 00:00:01,210
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,210 --> 00:00:02,240
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:02,240 --> 00:00:03,310
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:04,140 --> 00:00:07,650
(A: DNA Test Consultation,
B: Sample Collection, C: Results)

5
00:00:07,780 --> 00:00:09,310
(The DNA from the bloodstain...)

6
00:00:09,380 --> 00:00:11,280
(doesn't match Park Tae Ho.)

7
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:14,750
They don't match?

8
00:00:17,390 --> 00:00:19,490
Then it wasn't Park Tae Ho either?

9
00:00:22,330 --> 00:00:25,160
I remembered something
from back then,

10
00:00:25,960 --> 00:00:29,670
but I'm not sure
if it's a real memory.

11
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:32,300
What did you remember?

12
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:35,010
Someone tried to kill me.

13
00:00:35,340 --> 00:00:36,880
They were choking me.

14
00:00:37,410 --> 00:00:39,680
Other than Oh Jung Ran,
was there anyone else...

15
00:00:40,810 --> 00:00:42,650
who wanted me dead 30 years ago?

16
00:00:44,920 --> 00:00:46,050
Of course not.

17
00:00:47,120 --> 00:00:50,420
Your mind must be playing tricks
on you.

18
00:00:53,190 --> 00:00:54,190
I see.

19
00:00:55,930 --> 00:00:56,930
Understood.

20
00:01:21,450 --> 00:01:22,520
It wasn't him?

21
00:01:23,460 --> 00:01:25,860
Wait, so Park Tae Ho
really isn't the killer?

22
00:01:28,430 --> 00:01:29,690
That's what the test results say.

23
00:01:31,360 --> 00:01:33,530
Oh, what a relief.
Thank you so much.

24
00:01:34,870 --> 00:01:35,870
What was that?

25
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:38,340
Well, the fact
that it's not Park Tae Ho...

26
00:01:38,800 --> 00:01:40,470
is a huge relief for Dan Hui.

27
00:01:40,740 --> 00:01:42,240
Sure, it is a relief.

28
00:01:42,610 --> 00:01:45,640
But it's not entirely good news.

29
00:01:46,410 --> 00:01:49,580
We still don't know
who killed Myung Hui.

30
00:01:50,110 --> 00:01:52,120
And there was
no one else there that day.

31
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:55,120
Is it really not Park Tae Ho?

32
00:01:55,450 --> 00:01:58,120
Why? Are you doubting the results
this time too?

33
00:01:58,560 --> 00:02:00,660
You think he knew in advance
and pulled some strings?

34
00:02:00,790 --> 00:02:02,590
When we ran the tests
on Oh Jung Ran,

35
00:02:02,660 --> 00:02:05,030
you said there was nothing wrong
with the lab.

36
00:02:05,700 --> 00:02:06,700
That's right.

37
00:02:07,030 --> 00:02:08,030
That's true, but...

38
00:02:09,170 --> 00:02:11,270
We need to be careful
when it comes to Chairman Park.

39
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,240
At the warehouse
and during the police investigation,

40
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:16,410
we let our guard down
and got played.

41
00:02:17,140 --> 00:02:18,580
But I doubt it's the case this time.

42
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:20,810
How would Park Tae Ho know
to tamper with it?

43
00:02:20,980 --> 00:02:24,220
Anyway, I'll give these results
to Dan Hui.

44
00:02:25,020 --> 00:02:28,350
Now that we know,
I can easily tell her.

45
00:02:28,490 --> 00:02:31,360
Right. Ms. Kim is probably waiting.

46
00:02:32,190 --> 00:02:35,790
She seemed to suspect Park Tae Ho,
so I told her we were running tests.

47
00:02:36,690 --> 00:02:39,200
Then she must be waiting.
I should get going.

48
00:02:39,460 --> 00:02:41,630
- Right, okay. Sure.
- Go on.

49
00:02:41,630 --> 00:02:43,500
- I'm off.
- See you later.

50
00:02:48,910 --> 00:02:50,610
Still, just in case,

51
00:02:50,880 --> 00:02:53,210
I'll double-check with the lab
one more time.

52
00:02:53,380 --> 00:02:55,980
Okay, do that.
Let us know if anything seems off.

53
00:02:56,380 --> 00:02:57,380
Sure.

54
00:03:08,990 --> 00:03:11,400
Thank goodness it's not Park Tae Ho.

55
00:03:11,930 --> 00:03:14,500
I know. The whole time
we were running the tests,

56
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:16,230
I was hoping it wasn't him.

57
00:03:17,570 --> 00:03:18,970
He's still Min Jun's father,

58
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:22,010
and he's the man you've been with
for 30 years.

59
00:03:23,270 --> 00:03:24,280
That would've been tragic.

60
00:03:25,110 --> 00:03:26,580
If a higher power exists,
it wouldn't allow it.

61
00:03:27,250 --> 00:03:29,210
It's a relief
that it's not Park Tae Ho,

62
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:33,050
but will we be able to find
who killed Myung Hui?

63
00:03:33,420 --> 00:03:35,190
Well, about that...

64
00:03:35,850 --> 00:03:37,760
What if we use Park Tae Ho?

65
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:39,260
Use him?

66
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:41,530
He might not be the killer,

67
00:03:41,530 --> 00:03:44,100
but he still knows the most
about what happened 30 years ago.

68
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:48,330
What if we tell him the truth and
ask him to help us find the killer?

69
00:03:48,470 --> 00:03:50,030
I already tried to sound him out,

70
00:03:50,500 --> 00:03:53,570
but he seemed completely clueless
about what happened 30 years ago.

71
00:03:53,570 --> 00:03:54,740
Still...

72
00:03:55,310 --> 00:03:56,910
If he decides to look into it,

73
00:03:56,910 --> 00:03:59,210
don't you think
he might find something?

74
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:16,490
The one who deceived my mother
30 years ago...

75
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:20,870
and ended up making everyone
in this family miserable.

76
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:24,070
What is it?

77
00:04:24,370 --> 00:04:25,440
Father.

78
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:29,570
Don't you feel any guilt
toward Mother and me?

79
00:04:29,640 --> 00:04:32,280
Are you throwing a fit
because I stripped you and her...

80
00:04:32,740 --> 00:04:33,880
of your positions?

81
00:04:33,980 --> 00:04:35,780
Never mind my life,

82
00:04:36,480 --> 00:04:38,650
but her life was the one
that was truly pitiful.

83
00:04:39,420 --> 00:04:40,420
What?

84
00:04:40,820 --> 00:04:42,090
I'll be the one...

85
00:04:42,990 --> 00:04:46,960
you drag along
for your greed over the Adele Group.

86
00:04:47,030 --> 00:04:48,330
Just please...

87
00:04:48,390 --> 00:04:51,900
let Mother go
so she can start a new life.

88
00:04:52,660 --> 00:04:54,830
What kind of nonsense is this?

89
00:04:54,900 --> 00:04:56,730
For Mother's sake,

90
00:04:58,100 --> 00:05:00,670
can you at least pretend
you'll consider it?

91
00:05:09,310 --> 00:05:13,480
Unbelievable.
This family is falling apart.

92
00:05:14,620 --> 00:05:16,150
This can't go on.

93
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:20,260
I can't just let
Kim Myung Hui and Chloe be.

94
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:22,530
- Mrs. Ok!
- Yes, sir.

95
00:05:24,330 --> 00:05:25,360
Make sure...

96
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:29,270
everyone gathers tomorrow morning
without exception.

97
00:05:29,430 --> 00:05:31,470
Yes, I understand.

98
00:05:46,780 --> 00:05:48,850
Why did you stop everyone
on their way to work...

99
00:05:49,290 --> 00:05:50,790
so early in the morning?

100
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:53,160
Everything's a mess at home...

101
00:05:54,190 --> 00:05:56,690
and at the company,
so I'm going to clean things up.

102
00:05:57,730 --> 00:05:58,830
First, Kim Myung Hui.

103
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:01,570
You'll move back into
the main house.

104
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:03,970
Hold on.

105
00:06:04,670 --> 00:06:06,600
Have you lost your mind
just like she did?

106
00:06:06,670 --> 00:06:08,040
How can you trust her enough...

107
00:06:08,110 --> 00:06:09,870
to let her in the main house
when you should be kicking her out?

108
00:06:09,940 --> 00:06:11,480
When it comes to
being untrustworthy,

109
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:13,680
you're all the same.

110
00:06:15,110 --> 00:06:18,480
I'm going back to how things were,
restoring the balance.

111
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,550
The balance?

112
00:06:20,520 --> 00:06:21,520
Manager Kang.

113
00:06:21,920 --> 00:06:22,950
Yes, sir.

114
00:06:25,290 --> 00:06:26,890
- Report.
- Yes, sir.

115
00:06:28,490 --> 00:06:31,300
The divorce
between the chairman and Ms. Oh...

116
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:33,360
will be finalized soon.

117
00:06:34,370 --> 00:06:37,670
What are you talking about?
But I'm back now.

118
00:06:37,740 --> 00:06:39,800
Then the divorce
should be nullified.

119
00:06:39,870 --> 00:06:41,040
The chairman...

120
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:44,480
is going to file
for a marriage license with Ms. Kim.

121
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:46,640
A marriage license?

122
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:49,650
- Sir.
- Father.

123
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:51,550
Then,

124
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:55,890
are you saying you'll make
Min Jun the successor again?

125
00:06:58,990 --> 00:07:01,260
A marriage license?
Then what about me?

126
00:07:01,730 --> 00:07:03,490
What about me and Hyun Jun?

127
00:07:04,900 --> 00:07:08,430
Don't you get it?
We're going back to how things were.

128
00:07:08,930 --> 00:07:11,740
If anything's changed,
it's that you and Myung Hui...

129
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,770
have just switched places.

130
00:07:15,810 --> 00:07:19,610
What? Are you telling me
to live as your mistress?

131
00:07:21,610 --> 00:07:23,380
This is ridiculous.

132
00:07:23,780 --> 00:07:28,050
You might as well kill me.
No, I'd rather die than do that.

133
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:30,190
Keep this up and that will happen.

134
00:07:31,190 --> 00:07:33,260
It could put Hyun Jun
at a disadvantage...

135
00:07:33,320 --> 00:07:34,630
in the succession battle.

136
00:07:36,260 --> 00:07:38,900
Why are you taking it out
on him again?

137
00:07:41,730 --> 00:07:44,240
Park Min Jun, Park Hyun Jun.

138
00:07:44,870 --> 00:07:47,740
You two,
compete against each other again.

139
00:07:48,770 --> 00:07:53,310
Since you're both back
to being division directors,

140
00:07:53,710 --> 00:07:54,710
you're back to square one.

141
00:07:55,110 --> 00:07:56,510
Min Jun,

142
00:07:56,580 --> 00:08:00,820
prove that you've completely
moved on from the Temi Bio issue.

143
00:08:00,990 --> 00:08:02,050
Prove it?

144
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:05,190
Hyun Jun, get Chloe
to agree to a divorce...

145
00:08:05,860 --> 00:08:08,160
without a lawsuit
over the penalty fee.

146
00:08:08,590 --> 00:08:09,590
Father!

147
00:08:09,990 --> 00:08:13,600
All of you, stop plotting
to overthrow me.

148
00:08:15,700 --> 00:08:19,400
Try earning my approval instead...

149
00:08:22,470 --> 00:08:26,210
by dealing with the opponents
right in front of you.

150
00:08:42,460 --> 00:08:43,590
What's your reason?

151
00:08:44,330 --> 00:08:46,700
You don't trust me, so why...

152
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:48,700
That's right.

153
00:08:49,330 --> 00:08:51,440
I still don't trust you.

154
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:53,170
That's why...

155
00:08:54,570 --> 00:08:58,080
I'm determined to make you
one of my people.

156
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:59,410
One of your people?

157
00:08:59,410 --> 00:09:01,450
You said you decided to stand by me,

158
00:09:01,510 --> 00:09:03,450
even though you knew
I killed someone.

159
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:06,650
You said you held back
because I'm Min Jun's father.

160
00:09:09,050 --> 00:09:11,090
If we become
a legally married couple,

161
00:09:13,190 --> 00:09:15,090
you'll finally be on my side
for good.

162
00:09:18,300 --> 00:09:20,000
No matter how I think about it,
this is wrong.

163
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:23,030
After everything I did
to get you out of police custody?

164
00:09:24,100 --> 00:09:25,640
I can't stomach living
as a mistress,

165
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:28,470
and watching her become
the chairman's wife is even worse.

166
00:09:31,110 --> 00:09:33,580
You, why are you
just standing there?

167
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:36,310
Weren't you the one who couldn't
forgive him for killing someone?

168
00:09:36,710 --> 00:09:39,750
That's why you found Park Cheol Su
and turned them both in.

169
00:09:39,950 --> 00:09:41,390
And now you're marrying him?

170
00:09:41,750 --> 00:09:44,820
Do you really think you can live
as Park Tae Ho's wife?

171
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:52,100
Did Myung Hui die from the poison
you said you used,

172
00:09:52,330 --> 00:09:56,200
or was it someone else
who strangled her to death?

173
00:09:57,940 --> 00:09:59,770
Nothing's certain yet.

174
00:10:00,910 --> 00:10:04,440
That's why I can't stop here
or give up.

175
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:14,550
I'll do it.
I'll officially marry you.

176
00:10:16,090 --> 00:10:17,820
Kim Myung Hui, hey!

177
00:10:33,470 --> 00:10:35,410
Yes, this was processed at our lab.

178
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:39,380
Then can you double-check
if the test results are accurate?

179
00:10:39,710 --> 00:10:40,980
Well, this is strange,

180
00:10:41,050 --> 00:10:43,050
but the test records
have been deleted.

181
00:10:43,810 --> 00:10:44,820
What?

182
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:46,880
I tried contacting
the lab tech in charge,

183
00:10:47,080 --> 00:10:48,120
but she isn't getting back to me.

184
00:10:48,490 --> 00:10:50,290
She suddenly took a long-term leave.

185
00:10:51,790 --> 00:10:54,490
A sudden long-term leave?

186
00:10:54,560 --> 00:10:57,930
Once she's back,
I'll have her reach out to you.

187
00:11:04,670 --> 00:11:06,700
(Kim Jin Young)

188
00:11:15,950 --> 00:11:17,050
Hey, James.

189
00:11:17,450 --> 00:11:20,150
I checked.
The lab tech Kim Jin Young.

190
00:11:20,520 --> 00:11:23,990
She suddenly took a long-term leave
and even deleted the test records.

191
00:11:24,690 --> 00:11:26,460
It's all too suspicious.

192
00:11:26,860 --> 00:11:30,760
Please have the intel team find
her contact information or address.

193
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:33,000
Sure.

194
00:11:45,740 --> 00:11:49,480
Wait, you're kicking me out
of the master bedroom?

195
00:11:49,550 --> 00:11:53,750
The chairman told me
to redecorate it...

196
00:11:54,090 --> 00:11:55,620
to match his new wife's taste.

197
00:11:55,890 --> 00:11:56,950
His new wife?

198
00:11:58,190 --> 00:12:02,130
Now that you're a mistress,
you can't stay in the master.

199
00:12:02,490 --> 00:12:05,430
I doubt you'd want
Ms. Kim's old room anyway.

200
00:12:05,760 --> 00:12:08,800
Wouldn't you rather move
to the annex?

201
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:09,830
Hey!

202
00:12:10,030 --> 00:12:12,140
Come on. Not this again.

203
00:12:12,570 --> 00:12:16,040
You know it's no use yelling at me.

204
00:12:16,210 --> 00:12:19,040
Now, I have a lot to do,
so please leave.

205
00:12:19,310 --> 00:12:20,410
Please leave.

206
00:12:21,110 --> 00:12:22,410
Why, you...

207
00:12:23,610 --> 00:12:25,280
My goodness.

208
00:12:25,920 --> 00:12:26,980
That's enough.

209
00:12:28,350 --> 00:12:29,920
Please stop.

210
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:33,520
None of my outbursts are working.

211
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:36,730
Now I'm doomed to live with people
calling me a mistress.

212
00:12:37,760 --> 00:12:39,700
Even with the way things are now,

213
00:12:40,100 --> 00:12:41,570
are you still going
to hold onto Chloe?

214
00:12:41,630 --> 00:12:43,100
At the very least,
you have to beat Min Jun...

215
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:44,470
and take over as successor.

216
00:12:44,940 --> 00:12:48,340
You're the only hope I have left.

217
00:12:49,570 --> 00:12:52,610
I'll try to persuade Father
to give me a different set of terms.

218
00:12:53,240 --> 00:12:54,950
Breaking up with Chloe...

219
00:12:55,980 --> 00:12:57,150
is something I can't do.

220
00:12:59,020 --> 00:13:00,320
Hyun Jun.

221
00:13:01,050 --> 00:13:02,090
Park Hyun Jun.

222
00:13:06,860 --> 00:13:10,630
It's me. You promised
you'd break up Hyun Jun and Chloe.

223
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:13,860
Whatever you're planning,
do it fast. Just hurry up.

224
00:13:15,370 --> 00:13:17,870
I get it, so just be patient, okay?

225
00:13:32,280 --> 00:13:34,190
They charged a fortune,
claiming to be experts.

226
00:13:34,550 --> 00:13:35,790
And honestly, these look so real.

227
00:13:36,950 --> 00:13:40,490
With these, even Park Hyun Jun
will be completely fooled.

228
00:13:43,090 --> 00:13:45,000
Park Hyun Jun and Chloe.

229
00:13:45,730 --> 00:13:47,530
A rift will definitely form
between them.

230
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:00,310
What do you want?

231
00:14:00,310 --> 00:14:03,410
I wanted to talk about
how we're going to proceed.

232
00:14:04,250 --> 00:14:08,190
It seems Father wants us
to compete again,

233
00:14:09,250 --> 00:14:10,750
but nothing changes for us, right?

234
00:14:11,060 --> 00:14:14,260
Whoever becomes the next chairman
can still help Jin Ju.

235
00:14:14,260 --> 00:14:15,290
So?

236
00:14:16,090 --> 00:14:17,660
Are you here to tell me again...

237
00:14:17,730 --> 00:14:20,000
that I should break up with her
if I want to help her?

238
00:14:22,330 --> 00:14:23,400
Seriously.

239
00:14:24,740 --> 00:14:26,540
You people are unbelievable.

240
00:14:27,540 --> 00:14:29,970
Why is everyone telling me
to break up with her?

241
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:32,380
Why does everyone just say
whatever they want...

242
00:14:32,380 --> 00:14:33,880
and completely ignore my feelings?

243
00:14:35,680 --> 00:14:36,880
Hey, Min Jun.

244
00:14:37,410 --> 00:14:38,850
Was it easy for you
to forget Jin Ju?

245
00:14:38,950 --> 00:14:40,820
Even when they said she was dead,

246
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:43,790
you held on for 7 years. 7!

247
00:14:45,190 --> 00:14:48,930
But why do people expect me
to just get over her overnight?

248
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:53,760
This could hit me just as hard.
It might take years to get over.

249
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:56,100
Why?

250
00:14:56,770 --> 00:14:59,940
Why do you keep treating my feelings
like they're nothing...

251
00:15:01,170 --> 00:15:02,410
and just ignoring them?

252
00:15:07,380 --> 00:15:08,380
I'm sorry.

253
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:13,480
You're right.
I was dismissing your feelings.

254
00:15:15,490 --> 00:15:17,520
I can't deny it.

255
00:15:18,260 --> 00:15:19,290
I told you...

256
00:15:20,020 --> 00:15:23,090
that you were being selfish
and only thinking of yourself,

257
00:15:24,330 --> 00:15:27,770
but I was doing
the exact same thing.

258
00:15:28,170 --> 00:15:29,930
What are you trying to say now?

259
00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:32,400
Why the sudden apology?

260
00:15:32,900 --> 00:15:36,870
We used to be able to talk
without getting angry or fighting,

261
00:15:37,370 --> 00:15:40,180
and I was hoping we could
talk comfortably like that again.

262
00:15:40,740 --> 00:15:41,780
Lately,

263
00:15:43,210 --> 00:15:46,350
a friend who's like a brother,
a brother who's like a friend...

264
00:15:47,850 --> 00:15:48,890
is what I've needed.

265
00:15:50,620 --> 00:15:51,620
Brothers?

266
00:15:54,630 --> 00:15:56,530
We can't go back to how things were.

267
00:15:58,560 --> 00:16:00,960
Stop saying things
that just make it more awkward,

268
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:03,270
and get out.

269
00:16:13,580 --> 00:16:14,650
I don't have...

270
00:16:15,110 --> 00:16:17,510
any intention of getting
between you and Jin Ju.

271
00:16:18,780 --> 00:16:21,550
Let me know when you two
have a plan. That way...

272
00:16:22,750 --> 00:16:25,090
I can make my own plans accordingly.

273
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:29,190
It looks like I'll have a lot
on my plate from now on.

274
00:16:32,930 --> 00:16:33,930
I'll go,

275
00:16:34,830 --> 00:16:35,830
Hyun Jun.

276
00:16:44,610 --> 00:16:46,340
A friend who's like a brother,

277
00:16:47,540 --> 00:16:48,910
a brother who's like a friend?

278
00:16:52,180 --> 00:16:54,080
We can never go back to that.

279
00:16:55,550 --> 00:16:56,550
Because we're...

280
00:17:00,490 --> 00:17:01,860
not brothers anymore.

281
00:17:14,470 --> 00:17:15,540
This is it.

282
00:17:23,010 --> 00:17:24,010
Hello?

283
00:17:26,850 --> 00:17:28,190
Ms. Kim Jin Young?

284
00:17:29,890 --> 00:17:31,190
Ms. Kim Jin Young!

285
00:17:37,290 --> 00:17:39,060
You're going to meet Detective Yun?

286
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:42,570
Yes. He's someone who knows
what happened 30 years ago.

287
00:17:42,700 --> 00:17:45,570
Can't you just ask
Chairman Park first?

288
00:17:45,900 --> 00:17:49,410
Even if he says he didn't do it,
I can't fully trust him.

289
00:17:50,170 --> 00:17:52,810
I have to meet Detective Yun first
and confirm things.

290
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:54,980
Only then will I know
if Chairman Park's...

291
00:17:55,050 --> 00:17:56,580
being honest or not.

292
00:17:56,780 --> 00:17:59,820
All right.
I'll reach out to Detective Yun.

293
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:02,190
I'm not sure
he'll agree to meet, though.

294
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:15,470
Your memories have been coming back?

295
00:18:17,070 --> 00:18:18,370
Is that all it is?

296
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:21,310
I mean, you came looking for me
after 30 years,

297
00:18:21,310 --> 00:18:23,140
so I figured
something interesting was up.

298
00:18:24,310 --> 00:18:25,640
What a waste of time.

299
00:18:27,080 --> 00:18:29,780
Stories about the past
don't really interest me, so...

300
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:31,320
Thirty years ago,

301
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:34,320
you inspected the crime scene.

302
00:18:36,420 --> 00:18:37,750
The crime scene?

303
00:18:38,190 --> 00:18:42,190
You must already know that
Oh Jung Ran tried to kill me.

304
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:44,730
You must've inspected the villa...

305
00:18:44,730 --> 00:18:46,500
under orders
from Chairman Park Tae Ho.

306
00:18:47,460 --> 00:18:50,730
Did you find any clues at the scene?

307
00:18:51,070 --> 00:18:53,940
The story is that
Oh Jung Ran poisoned me,

308
00:18:54,910 --> 00:18:58,140
but my own memory tells me
someone was strangling me.

309
00:18:59,210 --> 00:19:02,480
I'm looking for the person
who choked me.

310
00:19:05,720 --> 00:19:07,020
So you're saying...

311
00:19:07,850 --> 00:19:11,520
it wasn't Oh Jung Ran,
but someone else...

312
00:19:12,020 --> 00:19:14,760
who tried to strangle you to death?

313
00:19:15,530 --> 00:19:16,590
Is that it?

314
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:18,760
Yes.

315
00:19:19,060 --> 00:19:21,870
I might be wrong about other things,
but definitely not this.

316
00:19:23,830 --> 00:19:25,170
But you're alive and kicking.

317
00:19:28,740 --> 00:19:30,940
I must've escaped from them.

318
00:19:31,910 --> 00:19:34,010
Was there anyone suspicious around
back then?

319
00:19:37,210 --> 00:19:40,880
Well, all I remember is going
to retrieve the body,

320
00:19:41,180 --> 00:19:42,320
and then dealing...

321
00:19:42,320 --> 00:19:44,190
with a massive headache
when it disappeared.

322
00:19:44,590 --> 00:19:45,590
Oh, right.

323
00:19:46,920 --> 00:19:48,830
I also remember
how you magically showed up alive...

324
00:19:49,290 --> 00:19:51,560
when you were supposed to be dead.

325
00:19:53,700 --> 00:19:54,700
I see.

326
00:19:55,900 --> 00:19:56,930
All right.

327
00:19:57,940 --> 00:20:00,900
If you remember anything,
please let me know.

328
00:20:10,910 --> 00:20:13,850
Someone strangled her?

329
00:20:15,990 --> 00:20:17,450
She was strangled?

330
00:20:21,890 --> 00:20:23,060
No way...

331
00:20:30,970 --> 00:20:31,970
Detective Yun.

332
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:34,440
Does he really know nothing,

333
00:20:35,210 --> 00:20:36,840
or is he just playing dumb?

334
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:40,610
To find out what happened
30 years ago,

335
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:43,150
do I need Park Tae Ho's help?

336
00:20:49,820 --> 00:20:51,390
Did you see the clothes?

337
00:20:51,690 --> 00:20:53,590
What? The clothes?

338
00:20:53,660 --> 00:20:55,430
The ones the chairman sent.

339
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:03,000
It's a gift to celebrate
your marriage registration.

340
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:06,070
The chairman expects you
to wear them to dinner.

341
00:21:07,170 --> 00:21:09,010
Yes, I understand.

342
00:21:09,570 --> 00:21:11,640
- I'll change and be right out.
- Sure.

343
00:21:33,030 --> 00:21:35,270
A dinner to celebrate
their marriage registration?

344
00:21:35,270 --> 00:21:36,330
Yes.

345
00:21:36,470 --> 00:21:39,740
They're filing the marriage papers
and having dinner.

346
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:43,010
I knew something was fishy
when he made you president.

347
00:21:43,070 --> 00:21:47,040
Now she's completely taking
your place as his wife.

348
00:21:48,380 --> 00:21:50,310
After everything I did
to snag that title?

349
00:21:50,810 --> 00:21:53,380
I've been fighting for 30 years
to hold onto it.

350
00:21:54,180 --> 00:21:57,490
I'm not losing it like this.
I have to go put a stop to it.

351
00:21:58,060 --> 00:22:01,260
There's no point in going.
You can't win.

352
00:22:01,660 --> 00:22:02,960
Just stay put.

353
00:22:04,130 --> 00:22:05,800
I'm so frustrated.

354
00:22:07,130 --> 00:22:08,900
I can't back down anymore.

355
00:22:09,830 --> 00:22:12,040
She isn't taking Adele Group
from me.

356
00:22:12,670 --> 00:22:16,070
Hyun Jun has to take over,
no matter what.

357
00:22:16,540 --> 00:22:19,280
His life is about to get
a whole lot harder.

358
00:22:27,420 --> 00:22:31,290
- Detective Yun.
- I told you, I'm not a detective!

359
00:22:31,350 --> 00:22:32,890
Right, of course.

360
00:22:33,120 --> 00:22:36,360
Deputy Chief Yun,
what brings you here unannounced?

361
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:41,670
What did you do to Kim Myung Hui
30 years ago?

362
00:22:42,270 --> 00:22:43,530
What are you talking about,

363
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:45,370
showing up out of the blue
like this?

364
00:22:45,470 --> 00:22:49,910
Tell me about it.
Just hearing her name makes me sick.

365
00:22:49,970 --> 00:22:52,810
Anyway, at the time,
the two of you...

366
00:22:53,180 --> 00:22:55,910
were convinced
you'd finished off Kim Myung Hui.

367
00:22:55,910 --> 00:22:57,480
We were.

368
00:22:57,980 --> 00:23:00,880
He screwed up and ruined it for us.

369
00:23:00,880 --> 00:23:03,550
I'm telling you, she was dead.

370
00:23:03,550 --> 00:23:04,920
Darn it.

371
00:23:06,390 --> 00:23:09,690
We should've used a stronger,
more effective poison back then.

372
00:23:11,700 --> 00:23:13,560
So you two thought...

373
00:23:13,960 --> 00:23:16,530
you killed her with poison.

374
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:19,700
But Kim Myung Hui...

375
00:23:21,770 --> 00:23:23,110
No way.

376
00:23:24,780 --> 00:23:26,880
Well, this is getting interesting.

377
00:23:26,940 --> 00:23:29,050
Very interesting indeed.

378
00:23:29,050 --> 00:23:30,910
What's so interesting?

379
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:34,250
Where's Chairman Park?
Is he in his office?

380
00:23:34,250 --> 00:23:36,120
He went to have dinner
with Ms. Kim...

381
00:23:37,190 --> 00:23:38,190
at the Korean restaurant nearby.

382
00:23:38,660 --> 00:23:40,190
Why are you looking for him?

383
00:23:41,460 --> 00:23:43,190
- What?
- What?

384
00:23:43,790 --> 00:23:45,430
Hey, what's this about?

385
00:23:46,800 --> 00:23:49,330
First Kim Myung Hui,
and now Detective Yun.

386
00:23:50,100 --> 00:23:51,740
Why are they asking about
what happened 30 years ago?

387
00:23:58,910 --> 00:24:00,740
(Park Hyun Jun, Head of Division 2)

388
00:24:01,550 --> 00:24:03,180
Sir, this arrived for you,

389
00:24:03,680 --> 00:24:05,480
but there's no sender.

390
00:24:06,350 --> 00:24:07,920
All right, I'll take a look.

391
00:24:08,320 --> 00:24:09,390
Yes, sir.

392
00:24:27,540 --> 00:24:29,910
(Division 2 Director's Office)

393
00:24:30,970 --> 00:24:33,040
I wonder if he'll like my gift.

394
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:36,850
Your incredible devotion to Chloe...

395
00:24:37,480 --> 00:24:39,050
I wonder how long it'll last.

396
00:24:41,850 --> 00:24:43,520
It's bound to fall apart anyway,

397
00:24:45,160 --> 00:24:46,320
so don't try so hard.

398
00:25:11,050 --> 00:25:12,120
Ms. Kim Jin Young?

399
00:25:16,520 --> 00:25:17,820
You're Kim Jin Young, right?

400
00:25:20,020 --> 00:25:22,530
Just a second. Ms. Kim!

401
00:25:24,790 --> 00:25:25,800
Stop right there!

402
00:25:50,190 --> 00:25:52,590
You're here.
Come on over, have a seat.

403
00:25:59,730 --> 00:26:00,730
Right.

404
00:26:03,100 --> 00:26:04,600
Just sign right there.

405
00:26:06,570 --> 00:26:08,910
(Marriage Registration)

406
00:26:10,140 --> 00:26:11,140
What's wrong?

407
00:26:11,980 --> 00:26:13,580
Are you having second thoughts?

408
00:26:29,430 --> 00:26:32,300
You forged the test results,
didn't you?

409
00:26:33,160 --> 00:26:34,360
Tell me the truth.

410
00:26:34,830 --> 00:26:37,370
Why are you doing this to me?

411
00:26:43,770 --> 00:26:44,770
Of course not.

412
00:26:46,840 --> 00:26:49,650
(Marriage Registration)

413
00:26:59,720 --> 00:27:01,590
Good. Very good.

414
00:27:02,990 --> 00:27:04,930
Now, with this,

415
00:27:05,530 --> 00:27:07,200
our marriage is truly official.

416
00:27:08,370 --> 00:27:10,200
I've asked Min Jun to join us,

417
00:27:10,630 --> 00:27:12,700
so we can celebrate
becoming a real family...

418
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:15,610
by having a nice meal together.

419
00:27:16,810 --> 00:27:19,210
Okay? And one more thing.

420
00:27:25,680 --> 00:27:26,750
This.

421
00:27:27,520 --> 00:27:29,690
A day like this calls
for a wedding gift.

422
00:27:30,350 --> 00:27:33,490
Rather than a gift,
I'd like the key to your P.O. box.

423
00:27:34,760 --> 00:27:38,160
You promised to hand over
the slush fund ledger.

424
00:27:39,030 --> 00:27:41,970
Come on, things are different now.

425
00:27:44,930 --> 00:27:47,640
Once you're completely mine...

426
00:27:49,240 --> 00:27:51,780
and I know I can trust you,
I'll give it to you.

427
00:28:02,120 --> 00:28:04,690
Then I'll accept this with the key.

428
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:12,160
And there's something
I need to tell you.

429
00:28:13,400 --> 00:28:14,400
Sure.

430
00:28:16,670 --> 00:28:17,670
Whatever it is, just tell me.

431
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:20,070
Thirty years ago...

432
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:28,780
(Incoming call: Chloe)

433
00:28:30,810 --> 00:28:33,720
I have to take this.
Excuse me for a second.

434
00:28:33,980 --> 00:28:35,350
Right. Sure thing.

435
00:29:10,450 --> 00:29:11,450
By any chance,

436
00:29:12,560 --> 00:29:14,860
is Kim Myung Hui
actually Kim Dan Hui?

437
00:29:16,390 --> 00:29:17,490
What are you talking about?

438
00:29:18,430 --> 00:29:20,860
Kim Myung Hui came to see me.

439
00:29:21,430 --> 00:29:24,130
She said someone had tried
to strangle her to death.

440
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:28,470
But on the day
she showed up with the baby,

441
00:29:28,810 --> 00:29:30,710
her neck was perfectly clean.

442
00:29:31,270 --> 00:29:32,980
If she'd been strangled that hard,

443
00:29:33,680 --> 00:29:35,510
it definitely would've left a mark.

444
00:29:37,610 --> 00:29:39,550
It appears that Kim Myung Hui died,

445
00:29:39,850 --> 00:29:41,850
and it was Kim Dan Hui
who showed up instead.

446
00:29:43,290 --> 00:29:44,290
Am I wrong?

447
00:29:46,690 --> 00:29:48,660
After all, you and I
both know very well...

448
00:29:49,490 --> 00:29:52,030
that Kim Myung Hui
and Kim Dan Hui...

449
00:29:52,930 --> 00:29:54,030
are twins.

450
00:30:03,410 --> 00:30:05,110
(Orphanage)

451
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:07,080
(President Park Tae Ho)

452
00:30:07,080 --> 00:30:09,010
Kim Myung Hui and Kim Dan Hui?

453
00:30:10,210 --> 00:30:12,350
Kim Myung Hui has a twin sister?

454
00:30:12,780 --> 00:30:15,590
Yes. I found her by digging through
scattered records...

455
00:30:15,650 --> 00:30:16,990
from the orphanage.

456
00:30:17,490 --> 00:30:18,520
Oh, right.

457
00:30:20,760 --> 00:30:21,760
And there's this.

458
00:30:22,590 --> 00:30:25,760
Kim Dan Hui was recently registered
as deceased.

459
00:30:26,130 --> 00:30:28,130
Recently deceased?

460
00:30:28,830 --> 00:30:32,840
Apparently, it was on the exact day
Kim Myung Hui appeared...

461
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:35,000
with the baby.

462
00:30:36,210 --> 00:30:39,240
It seems your intuition
is even sharper...

463
00:30:39,240 --> 00:30:40,880
than a detective's, sir.

464
00:30:41,240 --> 00:30:44,210
I didn't get why you wanted me
to keep investigating...

465
00:30:44,210 --> 00:30:45,850
after Kim Myung Hui came back.

466
00:30:45,950 --> 00:30:47,650
But as I kept digging,

467
00:30:47,950 --> 00:30:49,350
I started to realize
something was fishy.

468
00:30:52,320 --> 00:30:54,390
(President Park Tae Ho)

469
00:30:54,790 --> 00:30:55,860
Here.

470
00:30:57,890 --> 00:30:59,900
Shut your mouth,
drop it, and back off.

471
00:31:00,260 --> 00:31:03,370
I'll handle this myself from now on.

472
00:31:10,440 --> 00:31:13,040
(Orphanage, The late Kim Dan Hui)

473
00:31:18,820 --> 00:31:21,480
What exactly are you getting at?

474
00:31:24,150 --> 00:31:28,090
I think the real Kim Myung Hui died
back then.

475
00:31:28,730 --> 00:31:33,130
What if she wasn't poisoned,
but strangled to death instead?

476
00:31:34,430 --> 00:31:38,200
And the person
who strangled her to death...

477
00:31:40,800 --> 00:31:41,800
It was you, wasn't it?

478
00:31:52,620 --> 00:31:55,180
I thought you were just
some money-grubbing punk,

479
00:31:55,850 --> 00:31:56,950
but I'm impressed.

480
00:31:58,920 --> 00:31:59,920
Detective Yun.

481
00:32:03,030 --> 00:32:04,030
That's right.

482
00:32:06,030 --> 00:32:08,160
I killed Kim Myung Hui.

483
00:32:46,570 --> 00:32:49,570
(Pearl in Red)

484
00:32:49,570 --> 00:32:51,370
I can't believe
I was used and fooled...

485
00:32:51,370 --> 00:32:52,980
by the very man
who killed my sister!

486
00:32:53,380 --> 00:32:55,910
It makes me feel
so miserable and pathetic.

487
00:32:56,210 --> 00:32:59,450
Did Kim Dan Hui
finally figure everything out?

488
00:32:59,550 --> 00:33:01,850
I need to act
before she tries something.

489
00:33:01,850 --> 00:33:04,090
Hey, just because
I let you blackmail me for a bit...

490
00:33:04,090 --> 00:33:06,360
doesn't mean you have
any power here.

491
00:33:06,390 --> 00:33:07,790
Wake up.

492
00:33:08,090 --> 00:33:11,430
Min Jun and Chloe could betray you
at any time, you know.

493
00:33:11,860 --> 00:33:14,660
I'll show them exactly
what a nobody like me can do.

494
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:16,600
Just watch.

495
00:33:16,900 --> 00:33:18,900
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
